cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with fitting a 3D morphable model to single face images using geometric features, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of edges and landmark points, which are common in graphics and visualization, suggesting cs.GR (Graphics) as the second likely sub-category. The use of a morphable model involves manipulating 3D shapes, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are common in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach that relies on explicit hard correspondences, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
